We are using pathfinding for our autonomous routes. However, when we command the robot to go to an AprilTag, it sometimes takes the opposite path, moving uncontrollably to the other side of the arena. However, most of the time, it works normally. This issue mainly occurs when the code runs for the first time.

Have you made sure to set the proper alliance? You will want to go to a different AprilTag id depending on whether you are on the red or blue side of the field. Something like
var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance()
if (alliance.isNull()) {
  return 10; // No alliance currently, depends on practice field setup
}
if (DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.RED) {
  return 10
} else {
  return 21
}
To help you any more I would need to see the code.

We had a similar issue where our alliance wasn’t being set properly and we found out the solution was to defer the command that gets your alliance. That probably isn’t the fix for you guys and it’d be great if u could post relevant code.

Also, I’d suggest writing some code to make path finding impossible if your robot is on the other side of the field.
public static Alliance allianceFromPose(Pose2d pose) { return pose.getX() > LENGTH.in(Meters) / 2 ? Alliance.Red : Alliance.Blue; }
And use it in your path finding logic.
